ENTRY       EC 3.7.1.13                 Enzyme
NAME        2-hydroxy-6-oxo-6-(2-aminophenyl)hexa-2,4-dienoate hydrolase;
            CarC
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on carbon-carbon bonds;
            In ketonic substances
SYSNAME     (2E,4E)-6-(2-aminophenyl)-2-hydroxy-6-oxohexa-2,4-dienoate acylhydrolase
REACTION    (2E,4E)-6-(2-aminophenyl)-2-hydroxy-6-oxohexa-2,4-dienoate + H2O = anthranilate + (2E)-2-hydroxypenta-2,4-dienoate
ALL_REAC    (other) R05365
SUBSTRATE   (2E,4E)-6-(2-aminophenyl)-2-hydroxy-6-oxohexa-2,4-dienoate;
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     anthranilate [CPD:C00108];
            (2E)-2-hydroxypenta-2,4-dienoate
COMMENT     This enzyme catalyses the third step in the aerobic degradation pathway of carbazole. The effect of the presence of an amino group or hydroxyl group at the 2-position of the substrate is small. The enzyme has no cofactor requirement [2].
